{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Vd6vSonaBjj3rFwPZYBsWa","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# F6 Plan\n2\t\n3\t## Acceptance criteria\n4\t\n5\tFrom SPEC §6.1 — `POST /api/events/batch`:\n6\t\n7\t- Ingests an array of events.\n8\t- Same validation per event (as `POST /api/events`): `event_name` required; at least one of `device_id` or `user_id` required; `timestamp` optional (defaults to server time); `properties` optional.\n9\t- Identity resolution runs per event (same rules as single-event ingestion: insert mapping if both identifiers present, 409 on conflict).\n10\t- Returns `{ ok: number, errors: Array<{index, error}> }`.\n11\t\n12\t## Dependencies\n13\t\n14\tCompleted features this builds on:\n15\t- **F1** (`src/lib/clickhouse.ts`) — ClickHouse client singleton\n16\t- **F2** (`scripts/migrate.ts`, `scripts/schema.sql`) — database and tables\n17\t- **F4** (`src/lib/identity.ts`) — `validateEvent`, `insertEvent`, `IdentityConflictError`\n18\t- **F5** (`src/app/api/events/route.ts`) — single-event POST route (pattern to follow)\n19\t\n20\tAll confirmed done via `features/F*-done.md` sentinel files.\n21\t\n22\t## Files to create or modify\n23\t\n24\t- CREATE `src/app/api/events/batch/route.ts` — POST handler for batch ingestion\n25\t- CREATE `src/app/api/events/batch/__tests__/route.test.ts` — unit tests for the batch route\n26\t\n27\t## Implementation order\n28\t\n29\t1. **Create `src/app/api/events/batch/route.ts`** — POST handler that:\n30\t   - Parses request body as JSON.\n31\t   - Validates the body is an array; returns 400 if not.\n32\t   - Iterates over the array, calling `insertEvent` for each item.\n33\t   - Collects per-event results: increments `ok` on success, pushes `{ index, error }` on validation or conflict errors.\n34\t   - Returns JSON `{ ok, errors }` with status 200 (or 400 if body is not an array).\n35\t\n36\t2. **Create `src/app/api/events/batch/__tests__/route.test.ts`** — unit tests mocking `insertEvent` (same pattern as `src/app/api/events/__tests__/route.test.ts`).\n37\t\n38\t## Sprint contract\n39\t\n40\t- [ ] File `src/app/api/events/batch/route.ts` exists and exports `POST`\n41\t- [ ] Test suite → `pnpm test` exits 0 with 0 failures\n42\t- [ ] Lint → `pnpm lint` exits 0\n43\t- [ ] Type check → `pnpm typecheck` exits 0\n44\t- [ ] Build → `pnpm build` exits 0\n45\t\n46\t## Test plan\n47\t\n48\t- **Test file**: `src/app/api/events/batch/__tests__/route.test.ts`\n49\t- **Module under test**: `POST` from `src/app/api/events/batch/route.ts`\n50\t- **Cases to cover**:\n51\t  - All events valid → returns `{ ok: N, errors: [] }` with HTTP 200\n52\t  - Mixed valid/invalid events → returns correct `ok` count and `errors` array with correct `index` and `error` message for each failure\n53\t  - Identity conflict (409 from `insertEvent`) on one event → that event appears in `errors` with its conflict message; other events still succeed\n54\t  - Empty array → returns `{ ok: 0, errors: [] }`\n55\t  - Body is not an array (e.g. single object) → returns 400 with `{ error: \"...\" }`\n56\t  - Body is not valid JSON → returns 400 with `{ error: \"...\" }`\n57\t- **Integration gap**: HTTP check of `POST /api/events/batch` against running dev server — requires dev server\n58\t\n59\t## Risks and open questions\n60\t\n61\t1. **HTTP status code for partial success**: The spec says the route returns `{ ok, errors }` but does not specify the HTTP status code when some events fail and some succeed. Plan: return 200 always when the body is a valid array (errors are reported per-event in the `errors` array), and 400 only when the top-level body format is wrong (not an array, not JSON).\n62\t2. **Sequential vs parallel insertion**: The spec doesn't specify whether events in a batch should be processed sequentially or in parallel. Plan: process sequentially to preserve ordering and ensure identity resolution conflicts are deterministic within a single batch. This is consistent with the identity resolution algorithm in §5 where order matters for conflict detection.\n63\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0724ef57-662a-4069-a60a-1ebd2f429e53","uuid":"6cd36eda-d16e-4e78-905f-a0ce2aee86f4","timestamp":"2026-04-15T12:31:05.512Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/features/F6-plan.md","content":"# F6 Plan\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\nFrom SPEC §6.1 — `POST /api/events/batch`:\n\n- Ingests an array of events.\n- Same validation per event (as `POST /api/events`): `event_name` required; at least one of `device_id` or `user_id` required; `timestamp` optional (defaults to server time); `properties` optional.\n- Identity resolution runs per event (same rules as single-event ingestion: insert mapping if both identifiers present, 409 on conflict).\n- Returns `{ ok: number, errors: Array<{index, error}> }`.\n\n## Dependencies\n\nCompleted features this builds on:\n- **F1** (`src/lib/clickhouse.ts`) — ClickHouse client singleton\n- **F2** (`scripts/migrate.ts`, `scripts/schema.sql`) — database and tables\n- **F4** (`src/lib/identity.ts`) — `validateEvent`, `insertEvent`, `IdentityConflictError`\n- **F5** (`src/app/api/events/route.ts`) — single-event POST route (pattern to follow)\n\nAll confirmed done via `features/F*-done.md` sentinel files.\n\n## Files to create or modify\n\n- CREATE `src/app/api/events/batch/route.ts` — POST handler for batch ingestion\n- CREATE `src/app/api/events/batch/__tests__/route.test.ts` — unit tests for the batch route\n\n## Implementation order\n\n1. **Create `src/app/api/events/batch/route.ts`** — POST handler that:\n   - Parses request body as JSON.\n   - Validates the body is an array; returns 400 if not.\n   - Iterates over the array, calling `insertEvent` for each item.\n   - Collects per-event results: increments `ok` on success, pushes `{ index, error }` on validation or conflict errors.\n   - Returns JSON `{ ok, errors }` with status 200 (or 400 if body is not an array).\n\n2. **Create `src/app/api/events/batch/__tests__/route.test.ts`** — unit tests mocking `insertEvent` (same pattern as `src/app/api/events/__tests__/route.test.ts`).\n\n## Sprint contract\n\n- [ ] File `src/app/api/events/batch/route.ts` exists and exports `POST`\n- [ ] Test suite → `pnpm test` exits 0 with 0 failures\n- [ ] Lint → `pnpm lint` exits 0\n- [ ] Type check → `pnpm typecheck` exits 0\n- [ ] Build → `pnpm build` exits 0\n\n## Test plan\n\n- **Test file**: `src/app/api/events/batch/__tests__/route.test.ts`\n- **Module under test**: `POST` from `src/app/api/events/batch/route.ts`\n- **Cases to cover**:\n  - All events valid → returns `{ ok: N, errors: [] }` with HTTP 200\n  - Mixed valid/invalid events → returns correct `ok` count and `errors` array with correct `index` and `error` message for each failure\n  - Identity conflict (409 from `insertEvent`) on one event → that event appears in `errors` with its conflict message; other events still succeed\n  - Empty array → returns `{ ok: 0, errors: [] }`\n  - Body is not an array (e.g. single object) → returns 400 with `{ error: \"...\" }`\n  - Body is not valid JSON → returns 400 with `{ error: \"...\" }`\n- **Integration gap**: HTTP check of `POST /api/events/batch` against running dev server — requires dev server\n\n## Risks and open questions\n\n1. **HTTP status code for partial success**: The spec says the route returns `{ ok, errors }` but does not specify the HTTP status code when some events fail and some succeed. Plan: return 200 always when the body is a valid array (errors are reported per-event in the `errors` array), and 400 only when the top-level body format is wrong (not an array, not JSON).\n2. **Sequential vs parallel insertion**: The spec doesn't specify whether events in a batch should be processed sequentially or in parallel. Plan: process sequentially to preserve ordering and ensure identity resolution conflicts are deterministic within a single batch. This is consistent with the identity resolution algorithm in §5 where order matters for conflict detection.\n","numLines":63,"startLine":1,"totalLines":63}}}
